http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/Govt.-announces-27-new-Smart-Cities/article14600306.ece

 The government on Tuesday announced 27 cities as a new batch of Smart Cities. In the third round of competition, Venkaiah Naidu, the Minister for Urban Development, announced the list of new cities.Maharashtra tops the list with five cities — Aurangabad, Kalyan-Dombivli, Nagpur, Nashik and Thane — while Tamil Nadu and Karnatak come second with four cities each. Tamil Nadu has Madurai, Salem, Thanjavur and Vellore, while Karnataka has Hubli-Dharwad, Mangaluru, Shivamogga and Tumakuru.“I am happy to state that the transformational Smart City Plan is running ahead of schedule,” said Mr. Naidu.